To normalize the provided profile data, I'll follow the outlined normalization instructions for company names, job titles, skills, locations, and dates. Let's process the input profile:

```json
{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "title": "VP of Eng.",
  "location": "SF Bay Area",
  "key_skills": [
    "Python",
    "Data Sci.",
    "Machine Lrng"
  ],
  "experience": [
    {
      "company": "Tech Solutions Inc",
      "title": "VP Eng.",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "March 2018",
        "end_date": "Present",
        "date_range": "5 years 7 months"
      },
      "location": "San Francisco"
    },
    {
      "company": "Innovatech",
      "title": "Sr. Software Eng.",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "June 2015",
        "end_date": "February 2018",
        "date_range": "2 years 9 months"
      },
      "location": "San Francisco, CA"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Normalized Profile

```json
{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "title": "Vice President of Engineering",
  "location": "San Francisco Bay Area, California, United States",
  "key_skills": [
    "Python",
    "Data Science",
    "Machine Learning"
  ],
  "experience": [
    {
      "company": "Tech Solutions Inc.",
      "title": "Vice President of Engineering",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "2018-03",
        "end_date": "Present",
        "date_range": "5 years 7 months"
      },
      "location": "San Francisco, California, United States"
    },
    {
      "company": "Innovatech",
      "title": "Senior Software Engineer",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "2015-06",
        "end_date": "2018-02",
        "date_range": "2 years 9 months"
      },
      "location": "San Francisco, California, United States"
    }
  ],
  "normalization_notes": "Expanded abbreviations in job titles; Standardized location format; Added periods to company name 'Tech Solutions Inc.'"
}
```

### Explanation of Changes
1. **Job Titles**: Expanded "VP" to "Vice President" and "Eng." to "Engineering". Similarly, "Sr." was expanded to "Senior".
2. **Location**: "SF Bay Area" was expanded to "San Francisco Bay Area, California, United States". "San Francisco" and "San Francisco, CA" were standardized to "San Francisco, California, United States".
3. **Skills**: Expanded "Data Sci." to "Data Science" and "Machine Lrng" to "Machine Learning".
4. **Company Names**: Added a period to "Tech Solutions Inc." for consistency.
5. **Dates**: Converted all dates to the ISO format (YYYY-MM).

These changes ensure consistency and clarity across the profile data, making it suitable for clustering and analysis.
